        <div class="title"><i class="fa fa-info-circle"></i> What is Linked Data DoGi?</div>
        <div class="subtitle"></div>

        <a href="http://www.ittig.cnr.it/dogi/en/Index.php">DoGi</a> is a reference database of articles published in Italian legal journals. For each article, the DoGi record provides bibliographic information enhanced with: 

        <ul>
          <li>abstracts and/or summaries of articles;</li>
          <li>one or more classification codes based on the indexing DoGi system especially designed for legal subjects;</li>
          <li>a selection of legislative and jurisprudential references of the sources quoted in the article;</li>
          <li>further metadata describing more significant features of the article;</li>
          <li>link to the full text when freely available online.</li>
        </ul>
        <br />
        This web portal provides the bibliographic data of DoGi as <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Linked_data">Linked Open Data</a>.
